This paper is about text classification using a novel framework called JUMPER, which is a neural system that scans a piece of text sequentially and makes classification decisions at the time it wishes. This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are typically covered in the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses reinforcement learning (RL) to train the policy network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of JUMPER for image classification, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
